The paper introduces a novel approach for predicting the similarity score between two graphs using convolutional neural networks. This involves pairwise graph similarity computation, which is a challenging problem in computer science. The paper also demonstrates the use of Graph Edit Distance (GED) as an example metric. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves graph data structures and algorithms, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks for graph similarity search could also place the paper in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category.
